Fourth Department,

July, 1972

(July 6, 1972) First National Bank of Waterloo, Respondent, v. Arnold B. Glenn, Appellant.

Appeal dismissed for failure to prosecute, pursuant to rule 1000.3(b) (22 NYCRR 1000.3[b]). (Appeal from order of Monroe Special Term denying motion to dismiss complaint or transfer action.) Present — Del Vecchio, J. P., Witmer, Gabrielli, Cardamone and Henry, JJ.
